.TH "pch_udc_create_dma_chain" 9 "pch_udc_create_dma_chain" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pch_udc_create_dma_chain \- This function creates or reinitializes a DMA chain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pch_udc_create_dma_chain
.BI "(struct pch_udc_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "struct pch_udc_request *req "  ","
.BI "unsigned long buf_len "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
Reference to the endpoint structure
.IP "req" 12
Reference to the request
.IP "buf_len" 12
The buffer length
.IP "gfp_flags" 12
Flags to be used while mapping the data buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return codes:
0:              success,
-ENOMEM:        dma_pool_alloc invocation fails
